# CITADEL deep-scan backend — build-context exclusions
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IMPORTANT: this image is built from the REPOSITORY ROOT
# (`docker build -f citadel/server/Dockerfile .`), so the build context is the
# entire portfolio repo. We aggressively exclude everything that isn't the
# CITADEL app or backend to keep the context (and image) small and secret-free.
#
# Docker reads the .dockerignore next to the build context root by default; for
# a -f build it also honours <Dockerfile>.dockerignore — keep this file in sync
# if you relocate it. The patterns below are written for a repo-root context.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# VCS / CI
.git
.gitignore
.github
.gitlab-ci.yml

# Secrets & local env (never bake into the image)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
secrets*.json
aws-credentials*
*credentials*

# Node / build caches (deps are installed fresh via `npm ci` in the image)
node_modules
**/node_modules
npm-debug.log*
yarn-error.log
.npm
.cache
dist
coverage

# IaC & government deploy artifacts — not needed by the backend image
citadel/deploy
**/*.tf
**/*.tfvars
**/*.tfstate
**/*.tfstate.*
.terraform
.terraform.lock.hcl
**/*.bicep

# Docker meta
**/Dockerfile
**/.dockerignore
**/docker-compose.yml

# Large portfolio assets the backend neither runs nor serves
*.pdf
Resume_*.pdf

# Editor / OS cruft
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
